"""
b. i would say that version 3 is the most efficient because it utilizes the fact that if/elif/else statements are processed in order of which comes first and do not overlap. this allows the programmer to write out minimal code to have a complete program. 
"""
#Exercise 6:
purchase = int(input("Enter cost of purchase:$ "))
if purchase < 0:
  print("Invalid cost")
elif purchase >= 100:
  print("40% savings")
elif purchase >= 75:
  print("30% savings")
elif purchase >= 50:
  print("20% savings")
elif purchase >= 25:
  print("10% savings")
else:
  print("no savings")
